      "message": "[error] Line 4178: For peer-wide connection requests where the requested `deviceId` is empty, the pending entry is stored under `{peerId, emptyDeviceId}` but the callback looks it up with the callback\u0027s concrete `deviceId`. That leaves the pending entry uncleared after success/failure, so subsequent peer-wide retries are suppressed until expiration and stale entries can force unnecessary sockets later. Capture the originally requested device id separately and use it as the pending-map key, while still using the callback device id for message delivery.\n```suggestion\n        [w \u003d weak(), peerId, requestedDeviceId \u003d deviceId, connectionType, generation](const std::shared_ptr\u003cdhtnet::ChannelSocket\u003e\u0026 socket,\n                                                                                       const DeviceId\u0026 deviceId) {\n            dht::ThreadPool::io().run([w, peerId, requestedDeviceId, connectionType, generation, socket, deviceId] {\n                if (auto acc \u003d w.lock()) {\n                    bool retryOnFailure \u003d false;\n                    {\n                        std::lock_guard pendingLock(acc-\u003ependingMessageConnectionsMtx_);\n                        auto pending \u003d acc-\u003ependingMessageConnections_.find({peerId, requestedDeviceId});\n```\nIf retrying after a failure, pass `requestedDeviceId` back into `requestMessageConnection`; keep using `deviceId` only for `onPeerOnline`, `sendMessage`, and sync once a socket exists.",
